{
  "texts": [
    "Due to these limitations, some researchers, such as Eldan and Russinovich (2023); Chen and Yang (2023); Borkar (2023); Wu et al (2023); Wang et al (2023) prefer a second, more controllable but less realistic scenario, where forgetting is applied to an LLM fine-tuned with a dataset that includes the undesired knowledge.",
    "This allows for better control over the process, with the original, unaltered LLM serving as a baseline for comparison.",
    "However, this scenario risks unrealistic results due to the potential overfitting on the undesired knowledge.",
    "The assessment of model retaining often involves evaluating the utility difference of the LLM before and after the forgetting process on tasks different from the undesired knowledge.",
    "The smaller the utility difference, the better the retention."
  ]
}